+# TDDAB Plan: Implicit HEAD & OPTIONS for FastAPI
+**Date:** 2026-06-01
+
+<mission>
+Project: FastAPI (tiangolo), a Python web framework on top of Starlette + Pydantic.
+Python >=3.8, typing_extensions, `annotated_doc.Doc`. Tests use pytest + `from fastapi.testclient import TestClient`.
+Run tests: `python -m pytest tests/<file>.py -q` (pytest config: strict-markers, filterwarnings=error, timeout=20, ignores docs_src).
+
+GOAL: add two parameters `auto_head` and `auto_options` that produce implicit HEAD and OPTIONS
+behavior, plus a tracking middleware. Requirements (every one is graded):
+- Add `auto_head` and `auto_options` to FastAPI/APIRouter constructors, the HTTP decorators
+  (get/post/put/patch/delete/options/head/trace), `api_route`, `add_api_route`, and `include_router`
+  on BOTH `FastAPI` (applications.py) and `APIRouter` (routing.py).
+- `auto_head` defaults ON for GET routes; `auto_options` defaults OFF.
+- Direct app routes use app values as outermost default. Included-router routes resolve omitted
+  values by nearest non-omitted among route, include, router. Explicit HEAD/OPTIONS operations win.
+- Implicit HEAD preserves the GET route's dependencies, status, headers, validation; returns no body.
+- Implicit OPTIONS returns 200 JSON `{path, methods (ordered), operations}` and sends `Allow`.
+  `operations` matches OpenAPI for that path excluding HEAD and OPTIONS. One OPTIONS per path.
+- Method order constant: GET, HEAD, POST, PUT, PATCH, DELETE, OPTIONS, TRACE.
+- Public signatures exposing new params MUST use `Annotated[type, Doc("...")]`.
+- `ImplicitMethodTrackingMiddleware` in `fastapi/middleware/methods.py`; `get_stats()`/`reset_stats()`
+  return a deep copy shaped `{full_path: {"head_hits": int, "options_hits": int}}`, reset clears counts,
+  track implicit hits only, ignore non-HTTP scopes.
+
+ARCHITECTURE DECISIONS (final, no alternatives):
+- Sentinel for "omitted": `Default(None)` from `fastapi.datastructures` (a `DefaultPlaceholder`).
+  New params default to `Default(None)`. Constructors default to concrete `auto_head=True`,
+  `auto_options=False`.
+- `APIRoute` stores params RAW (`self.auto_head`, `self.auto_options`) â€” NOT resolved at add time,
+  so include precedence can resolve later.
+- `APIRouter.add_api_route` passes the raw values straight into `APIRoute` (no merge with self).
+- `APIRouter.include_router` resolves precedence with `_first_set(route.auto_head, auto_head_param,
+  router.auto_head)` (router param = the included sub-router) and passes the resulting CONCRETE value
+  to `add_api_route`, "baking" it so it won't fall back to the app default.
+- Implicit routes are generated lazily ONCE via a hook in `FastAPI.__call__`, calling
+  `self.router.generate_implicit_routes()` guarded by `self.router._implicit_generated`.
+- Generation groups `APIRoute`s by `route.path_format`. Implicit HEAD = `copy.copy` of the GET route
+  with `methods={"HEAD"}`, `include_in_schema=False`, `_fastapi_implicit="head"`, and a wrapped `.app`
+  that blanks the response body and sets scope flags. Implicit OPTIONS = a `starlette.routing.Route`
+  with `methods=["OPTIONS"]`, `include_in_schema=False`, endpoint closure computing the JSON.
+- Method ordering: module-level `METHOD_ORDER` list + `order_methods(set)` helper in routing.py.
+- Resolution helpers in routing.py: `_first_set(*vals)` returns first non-`DefaultPlaceholder` (else last),
+  `_resolve_auto(val, default)` returns `default` if val is `DefaultPlaceholder` else `bool(val)`.
+- Scope flags set by implicit handlers: `scope["fastapi_implicit_method"]` ("head"|"options") and
+  `scope["fastapi_implicit_path"]` (the route path_format). The middleware reads them after calling
+  the app and increments counters keyed by the path.
+
+Key existing code (routing.py): `APIRoute.__init__`@808 (methods normalized @886-888, `self.app`@972),
+`get_value_or_default` in fastapi/utils.py, `APIRouter.__init__`@1028, `add_api_route`@1332,
+`api_route`@1415, `include_router`@1574 (merge loop @1728), decorators get@1827/put/post/delete/options/
+head/patch/trace. applications.py: `FastAPI.__init__` builds `self.router=APIRouter(...)` @986,
+`__call__`@1157, decorators delegate to `self.router.*`. openapi/utils.py `get_openapi_path`@263 only
+emits operations for `include_in_schema` routes, iterating `route.methods`.
+
+Doc style example to copy:
+`x: Annotated[bool, Doc(""" ... """)] = Default(None)`
