+<block id="01-method-ordering">
+## TDDAB-1: Method ordering helper + resolution helpers
+
+<intro>
+Add module-level constants/helpers to `/app/fastapi/routing.py`, near the top after imports.
+Pure functions, no behavior change elsewhere. `DefaultPlaceholder` and `Default` are already imported.
+Create a new unit test file `/app/tests/test_implicit_method_order.py`.
+</intro>
+
+<red>
+- test: `order_methods({"POST","GET","OPTIONS"})` returns `["GET","POST","OPTIONS"]` (canonical order).
+- test: `order_methods({"TRACE","HEAD","GET"})` returns `["GET","HEAD","TRACE"]`.
+- test: `order_methods` places any unknown method (e.g. `"FOO"`) after all known ones, sorted.
+- test: `METHOD_ORDER == ["GET","HEAD","POST","PUT","PATCH","DELETE","OPTIONS","TRACE"]`.
+- test: `_first_set(Default(None), Default(None), True)` returns `True`; `_first_set(False, True)` returns `False`.
+- test: `_resolve_auto(Default(None), True)` returns `True`; `_resolve_auto(False, True)` returns `False`.
+</red>
+
+### Implementation
+In `/app/fastapi/routing.py` (module level):
+```python
+METHOD_ORDER = ["GET", "HEAD", "POST", "PUT", "PATCH", "DELETE", "OPTIONS", "TRACE"]
+
+def order_methods(methods):
+    known = [m for m in METHOD_ORDER if m in methods]
+    extra = sorted(m for m in methods if m not in METHOD_ORDER)
+    return known + extra
+
+def _first_set(*values):
+    for v in values:
+        if not isinstance(v, DefaultPlaceholder):
+            return v
+    return values[-1]
+
+def _resolve_auto(value, default):
+    if isinstance(value, DefaultPlaceholder):
+        return default
+    return bool(value)
+```
+
