+<block id="02-tracking-middleware">
+## TDDAB-2: ImplicitMethodTrackingMiddleware
+
+<intro>
+Create `/app/fastapi/middleware/methods.py` with a pure-ASGI middleware. It counts implicit HEAD/OPTIONS
+hits, which downstream implicit handlers signal via `scope["fastapi_implicit_method"]` and
+`scope["fastapi_implicit_path"]`. Independent block; no other file changes.
+Create test `/app/tests/test_implicit_middleware.py` driving the middleware with hand-built scopes.
+</intro>
+
+<red>
+- test: non-http scope (`{"type":"lifespan"}`) is passed straight to the wrapped app and recorded nothing in `get_stats()`.
+- test: an http call where the inner app sets `scope["fastapi_implicit_method"]="head"`, `scope["fastapi_implicit_path"]="/x"` increments `get_stats()["/x"]["head_hits"]` to 1 and leaves `options_hits` 0.
+- test: an http call setting `"options"` increments `options_hits`.
+- test: an http call where the inner app sets NO flag records nothing (explicit/normal routes not tracked).
+- test: two head hits on `/x` accumulate to `head_hits==2`.
+- test: `get_stats()` returns a deep copy â€” mutating the returned dict does not change internal state.
+- test: `reset_stats()` returns the current stats (deep copy) AND clears internal counts so a subsequent `get_stats()` is `{}`.
+</red>
+
+### Implementation
+`/app/fastapi/middleware/methods.py`:
+```python
+import copy
+from starlette.types import ASGIApp, Message, Receive, Scope, Send
+
+
+class ImplicitMethodTrackingMiddleware:
+    def __init__(self, app: ASGIApp) -> None:
+        self.app = app
+        self._stats: dict[str, dict[str, int]] = {}
+
+    async def __call__(self, scope: Scope, receive: Receive, send: Send) -> None:
+        if scope["type"] != "http":
+            await self.app(scope, receive, send)
+            return
+        await self.app(scope, receive, send)
+        method = scope.get("fastapi_implicit_method")
+        if method in ("head", "options"):
+            path = scope.get("fastapi_implicit_path", scope.get("path", ""))
+            entry = self._stats.setdefault(path, {"head_hits": 0, "options_hits": 0})
+            entry[f"{method}_hits"] += 1
+
+    def get_stats(self) -> dict:
+        return copy.deepcopy(self._stats)
+
+    def reset_stats(self) -> dict:
+        snapshot = copy.deepcopy(self._stats)
+        self._stats = {}
+        return snapshot
+```
+Test helper: a fake inner app `async def app(scope, receive, send): scope["fastapi_implicit_method"]="head"; scope["fastapi_implicit_path"]="/x"`. Build `mw = ImplicitMethodTrackingMiddleware(app)`, await `mw({"type":"http","path":"/x"}, recv, send)` with trivial `recv`/`send` coroutines.
+
+<success>
+- [ ] `python -m pytest tests/test_implicit_middleware.py -q` passes.
+- [ ] `get_stats`/`reset_stats` shape is exactly `{full_path: {"head_hits": int, "options_hits": int}}`.
+</success>
