+## TDDAB-6: Implicit HEAD generation + __call__ hook
+
+<intro>
+Implement `generate_implicit_routes` on `APIRouter` (HEAD portion only here) and hook it once from
+`FastAPI.__call__`. Files: `/app/fastapi/routing.py`, `/app/fastapi/applications.py`.
+Test: `/app/tests/test_implicit_head.py` (TestClient). Depends on blocks 01,03,04,05.
+HEAD route = `copy.copy` of the GET route, `methods={"HEAD"}`, `include_in_schema=False`,
+`_fastapi_implicit="head"`, `.app` wrapped to set scope flags and blank the body. Resolution of whether
+to add HEAD: `_resolve_auto(route.auto_head, self.auto_head)` for each GET route, only when no explicit
+HEAD operation exists at that path. `import copy` at top of routing.py if not present.
+</intro>
+
+<red>
+- test: GET `/items` returning `{"x":1}`; a HEAD request returns 200, empty body (`response.content == b""`), and the same `content-type` header as GET.
+- test: HEAD preserves dependencies â€” a GET route with a dependency that raises 400 makes HEAD also return 400.
+- test: HEAD preserves validation â€” GET with required query param, HEAD without it returns 422.
+- test: explicit HEAD wins â€” if user defines `@app.head("/items")` returning a 418, HEAD returns 418 (no implicit override).
+- test: `auto_head=False` on the GET route disables implicit HEAD â†’ HEAD returns 405.
+- test: app-level `FastAPI(auto_head=False)` disables HEAD for a plain `@app.get` route â†’ 405.
+- test: included router GET route still gets implicit HEAD (precedence baked) â†’ HEAD returns 200.
+- test: OpenAPI schema for `/items` has no `head` key (implicit route is `include_in_schema=False`).
+</red>
+
+### Implementation
+`/app/fastapi/routing.py`:
+```python
+import copy  # if not already imported
+
+def _make_head_app(original_app, path):
+    async def head_app(scope, receive, send):
+        scope["fastapi_implicit_method"] = "head"
+        scope["fastapi_implicit_path"] = path
+        async def send_wrapper(message):
+            if message["type"] == "http.response.body":
+                message = dict(message)
+                message["body"] = b""
+                message["more_body"] = False
+            await send(message)
+        await original_app(scope, receive, send_wrapper)
+    return head_app
+
+# method on APIRouter:
+def generate_implicit_routes(self):
+    if self._implicit_generated:
+        return
+    self._implicit_generated = True
+    groups = {}
+    order = []
+    for route in list(self.routes):
+        if isinstance(route, APIRoute) and not getattr(route, "_fastapi_implicit", None):
+            if route.path_format not in groups:
+                groups[route.path_format] = []
+                order.append(route.path_format)
+            groups[route.path_format].append(route)
+    new_routes = []
+    for path in order:
+        routes = groups[path]
+        explicit_methods = set()
+        for r in routes:
+            explicit_methods |= r.methods
+        add_head = False
+        if "HEAD" not in explicit_methods:
+            for r in routes:
+                if "GET" in r.methods and _resolve_auto(r.auto_head, self.auto_head):
+                    head_route = copy.copy(r)
+                    head_route.methods = {"HEAD"}
+                    head_route.include_in_schema = False
+                    head_route._fastapi_implicit = "head"
+                    head_route.app = _make_head_app(r.app, path)
+                    new_routes.append(head_route)
+                    add_head = True
+                    break
+        # OPTIONS handled in block 07
+    self.routes.extend(new_routes)
+```
+`/app/fastapi/applications.py` `FastAPI.__call__` (top, before `super().__call__`):
+```python
+if not self.router._implicit_generated:
+    self.router.generate_implicit_routes()
+```
