+operation at that path enables `auto_options` and there is no explicit OPTIONS. Files:
+`/app/fastapi/routing.py`. Test: `/app/tests/test_implicit_options.py` (TestClient). Depends on block 06.
+The OPTIONS endpoint returns 200 JSON `{path, methods (ordered), operations}` and an `Allow` header.
+`operations` = `app.openapi()["paths"][path]` minus `head`/`options` keys. `methods` = ordered union of
+explicit methods + HEAD (if HEAD will exist) + OPTIONS. Use `routing.Route(path, endpoint, methods=["OPTIONS"],
+include_in_schema=False)` and tag it `_fastapi_implicit="options"` (set as attribute after construction).
+</intro>
+
+<red>
+- test: GET `/items` with `auto_options=True` â†’ OPTIONS `/items` returns 200, JSON `path=="/items"`, `methods` ordered as `["GET","HEAD","OPTIONS"]`, and an `Allow` header equal to `"GET, HEAD, OPTIONS"`.
+- test: `operations` equals the app's OpenAPI path item for `/items` with `head`/`options` keys removed (compare against `app.openapi()["paths"]["/items"]`).
+- test: `auto_options` default OFF â†’ without enabling it, OPTIONS `/items` returns 405 (no implicit OPTIONS).
+- test: enabling on a non-GET route (`@app.post("/things", auto_options=True)`) yields an OPTIONS `/things` whose `methods` is `["POST","OPTIONS"]` (no HEAD).
+- test: exactly ONE OPTIONS route per path even when multiple operations on the path enable `auto_options` (count routes with `_fastapi_implicit=="options"` for the path == 1).
+- test: explicit OPTIONS wins â€” `@app.options("/items")` returning custom body is used; no implicit OPTIONS overrides it.
+- test: implicit OPTIONS route is absent from OpenAPI (`"options"` not under `/items` in `app.openapi()["paths"]`).
+- test: CORS preflight still works â€” with `CORSMiddleware` configured, an OPTIONS request carrying `access-control-request-method` returns CORS headers from the middleware (not the implicit JSON body).
+</red>
+
+### Implementation
+`/app/fastapi/routing.py`:
+```python
+def _make_options_endpoint(path, ordered_methods):
+    async def options_endpoint(request):
+        request.scope["fastapi_implicit_method"] = "options"
+        request.scope["fastapi_implicit_path"] = path
+        schema = request.app.openapi()
+        path_item = schema.get("paths", {}).get(path) or {}
+        operations = {
+            k: v for k, v in path_item.items() if k.lower() not in ("head", "options")
+        }
+        content = {"path": path, "methods": ordered_methods, "operations": operations}
+        return JSONResponse(
+            content, status_code=200, headers={"Allow": ", ".join(ordered_methods)}
+        )
+    return options_endpoint
+```
+In `generate_implicit_routes`, after the HEAD section for each path:
+```python
+add_options = False
+if "OPTIONS" not in explicit_methods:
+    for r in routes:
+        if _resolve_auto(r.auto_options, self.auto_options):
+            add_options = True
+            break
+if add_options:
+    methods_set = set(explicit_methods)
+    if add_head or "HEAD" in explicit_methods:
+        methods_set.add("HEAD")
+    methods_set.add("OPTIONS")
+    ordered = order_methods(methods_set)
+    opt_route = routing.Route(
+        path,
+        _make_options_endpoint(path, ordered),
+        methods=["OPTIONS"],
+        include_in_schema=False,
+    )
+    opt_route._fastapi_implicit = "options"
+    new_routes.append(opt_route)
+```
+(`add_head` is the boolean computed in the HEAD section; ensure it is in scope for the path loop.)
+`JSONResponse` is already imported in routing.py.
